Reading notes dated August 8 - October 11, 1995 on Oscar Cullmann's "Christ and Time: The Primitive Christian Conception of Time and History." Summarizes Cullmann's argument that early Christian faith centered on temporal distinctions (formerly/now/then) rather than spatial (here/beyond). Discusses NT terminology: kairos, aion, and the concept of redemptive history.

